text.name: Gasha ticket
text.desc: You can spin the gacha once at the Regnus Store.

text.name: 1st Anniversary Gasha Ticket
text.desc: A ticket commemorating the first anniversary of the launch of the "BLUE PROTOCOL" service. You can spin a special gacha.

text.name: Character name change ticket
text.desc: Change the character name on the character select screen

text.name: Team Name Change Ticket
text.desc: Change the name of your team at team registration

text.name: Warrior's Talisman
text.desc: Give it to the Class Master and he'll teach you the secrets of tactical skills.

text.name: Reward plus number of receipts
text.desc: Number of times you can receive "Reward Plus" for the target mission

text.name: Reward plus additional receipt ticket
text.desc: You can add one "reward plus number of receipts"

text.name: Number of times you have received support benefits
text.desc: The number of times you can receive "Support Benefits" for the target mission using the Matching Support function

text.name: M Takara Baito Ticket
text.desc: When used to clear a mission, you can double the amount of treasure chests dropped by enemies. The contents are randomly selected, so you won't get two of the same thing. The number of treasure chests obtained for achievements, etc. will not be doubled.

text.name: Season Pass Quest Completion Ticket
text.desc: You can complete daily and weekly quests in the Season Pass Quests. The number required varies depending on the quest.

text.name: Craft success rate x1.1 ticket
text.desc: When crafting with the Ball-Turning Ritual, the chance of a "Great Success" is increased by 1.1 times. The number required varies depending on the crafting target.

text.name: Ball-Turning Craft Success Guaranteed Ticket
text.desc: When crafting with the Ball-Turning Ritual, it will always be a "Great Success". The number required varies depending on the crafting target.

text.name: Tuning Ticket
text.desc: You can have a weapon modifier tune your ability plugs. The number required varies depending on the weapon.

text.name: Ability Effect Value Keep Ticket
text.desc: Tuning allows you to fix any ability effect value. The required amount varies depending on the weapon.

text.name: Weapon Socket 1 Expansion Ticket
text.desc: Allows a weapon modder to add an extra socket to your weapon

text.name: Weapon Socket 2 Expansion Ticket
text.desc: A weapon modder can add a second socket to your weapon

text.name: Weapon Socket 3 Expansion Ticket
text.desc: A weapon modder can add a third socket to your weapon.

text.name: Weapon Socket 4 Expansion Ticket
text.desc: A weapon modder can add a fourth socket to your weapon.

text.name: Ability Plug Removal Ticket
text.desc: You can have any socket's ability plug removed. The required number varies depending on the weapon.

text.name: Craft success rate x1.3 ticket
text.desc: When crafting with the Ball-Turning Ritual, the chance of a "Great Success" is increased by 1.3 times. The number required varies depending on the crafting target.

text.name: Ability Plug Recovery Ticket
text.desc: You can collect and reuse ability plugs from any socket. The number required varies depending on the weapon.

text.name: M Caravan Chance +1 Ticket
text.desc: Mount Caravan gives you an extra lucky chance

text.name: M Caravan Chance +3 Ticket
text.desc: Mount Caravan gives you 3 extra lucky chances

text.name: M Caravan Local Knowledge Increase Ticket
text.desc: You will gain familiarity with each Mount Caravan destination 5 times faster than with a regular dispatch.

text.name: M Caravan Dispatch Time Reduction Ticket
text.desc: Mounted Caravans can reduce dispatch time by 20%

text.name: M Caravan Dispatch Instant Completion Ticket
text.desc: Instantly complete a mission with Mount Caravan

text.name: M Caravan Dispatch Destination Addition Ticket
text.desc: Mount Caravan can instantly unlock the "Dungeon" destination.

text.name: Special Redraw Ticket - Advanced
text.desc: The weapon modifier can re-select the weapon's special effect. The special effect will be selected from rarities higher than the current special effect rarity.

text.name: Special Effect Redraw Ticket
text.desc: You can have the weapon modifier re-select the weapon's special effects.

text.name: Special Effect Value Upper Ticket
text.desc: A weapon modder can increase the weapon's special effect value by one level (cannot be used if the effect value is at its maximum)

text.name: Special Effect Value Redraw Ticket
text.desc: A weapon modifier can re-select the weapon's special effect value (cannot be used if the effect value is at its maximum)

text.name: Limit Break Weapon Replacement Ticket
text.desc: When performing limit break, it will replace the material weapon.

text.name: Weapon limit break success rate x1.1
text.desc: Increases the success rate of weapon limit breakthrough by 1.1 times.

text.name: Weapon limit break success rate 1.3 times can
text.desc: Increases the success rate of weapon limit breakthrough by 1.3 times.

text.name: Weapon Limit Break Success Guaranteed Can
text.desc: Weapon limit breakthrough is guaranteed to be successful.

text.name: Limit Break B-Imagine Replacement Ticket
text.desc: Substitutes for Battle Imagine materials when breaking through limits

text.name: B-1.1x success rate for limit breakthrough
text.desc: Increases the success rate of B-Imagine's limit breakthrough by 1.1 times.

text.name: B-1.3x success rate for limit breakthrough
text.desc: Increases the success rate of B-Imagine's limit breakthrough by 1.3 times.

text.name: B-Limit Break Success Guaranteed Can
text.desc: B-Imagine's limit-breaking will definitely be successful.

text.name: Limit Break E-Imagine Replacement Ticket
text.desc: When performing limit break, it replaces the material Enhance Imagine

text.name: E-Breakthrough success rate 1.1 times can
text.desc: Increases the success rate of E-Imagine limit breakthrough by 1.1 times.

text.name: E-Breakthrough success rate 1.3 times
text.desc: Increases the success rate of E-Imagine's limit breakthrough by 1.3 times.

text.name: E-Limit Break Success Guaranteed Can
text.desc: E-Imagine's limit breakthrough will always be successful.

text.name: Limit Break M-Imagine Replacement Ticket
text.desc: Replaces the mount Imagine material when breaking through limits

text.name: Regular beauty treatment ticket
text.desc: You can change your appearance, such as your hairstyle or body shape, at a beauty salon.

text.name: Type change beauty treatment ticket
text.desc: You can change your appearance, including your type, at a beauty salon.

text.name: Makeup change beauty treatment ticket
text.desc: You can change only your makeup at the beauty salon

text.name: Hairstyle change beauty salon ticket
text.desc: You can only change your hairstyle and color at the beauty salon.

text.name: Weapon Skin Exchange Ticket
text.desc: You can exchange them for your favorite weapon skins at the souvenir exchange.

text.desc: You can exchange them for whatever you like at the souvenir exchange. By exchanging them at your favorite singer's exchange, you will be supporting that singer.

text.name: Step Up Medal
text.desc: Medals can be obtained by spinning the 1st Anniversary Step-Up Gasha. They can be exchanged for various items at the commemorative item exchange.

text.name: Welcome Points
text.desc: You can get points by clearing the bonus tasks in the welcome event. You can get various rewards by collecting a certain amount.

text.name: Comeback Points
text.desc: Points can be obtained by clearing the bonus tasks in the comeback event. Various rewards will be given when a certain amount is collected.

text.name: Bapharia's seal
text.desc: You can exchange it for anything you like at the souvenir exchange.

text.name: Research Points
text.desc: Points can be obtained by performing actions specified in the event, such as gathering, hunting, and clearing missions. Various rewards will be given when a certain amount is collected.

text.name: Valkyrie Coin Red
text.desc: You can exchange them for various items at the souvenir exchange.
